 {"id":"flywheel_connectors-u2g49","title":"[REVIEW][MED] fcp-e2e/webhook_receiver: happy-path suite never proves endpoint listing behavior","description":"crates/fcp-e2e/tests/webhook_receiver_compliance_e2e.rs:453-500 claims an allow-path connector suite but only asserts report.passed plus invoke_status == Ok. The adapter invoke path delegates to connectors/webhook-receiver/src/connector.rs:533-556, where webhook.endpoints.list returns the current endpoint inventory, yet the test never seeds an endpoint and never asserts anything about the returned endpoints payload or state. The suite can pass while list behavior is wrong or empty. Fix: create an endpoint first or seed store state, then assert the returned endpoints payload (count and fields) rather than only harness status.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T18:20:23.568976Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-04-24T18:44:09.740612Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T18:44:09.740345Z","close_reason":"Resolved by commit b8d3ed69 (test(fcp-e2e/webhook_receiver): cover endpoint listing response shape + schema in happy-path suite)","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
